The Niger State governor, Alhaji Abubakar Sani Bello, is chairing the Caretaker/Extra-ordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) parley of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). Bello arrived the party Secretariat at noon was and was applauded by scores of party supporters and staff. He explained that there was nothing unusual over the parley with his colleagues in the caretaker committee. The Niger state governor was subsequently ushered into the National Working Committee (NWC) hall to await other members of the committee. Among those in attendance were the Secretary of the Committee, Senator John James Akpanudoedehe, the Women representative in CECPC, Stella Okotete, the Youth Leader, Ismail Ahmed and Mr David Lyon, Prof. Tahir Mamman, Senator Ali Abba, Sen. Ken Nnamani, Sen. Yusuf Yusuf.